-- ÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉÔĽÉ

Total : Sequence Ôäô Ôćĺ Type Ôäô
Total X = ╬ú[ n Ôłł ÔäĽ ] obj X n

-- PushRel as a ╬ú-type (no data declaration, no K issues, no warnings)
PushRel : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ Total X Ôćĺ Total X Ôćĺ Type Ôäô
PushRel X (n , a) (m , b) = ╬ú[ p Ôłł suc n Ôëí m ] PathP (╬╗ i Ôćĺ obj X (p i)) (map X a) b

-- Canonical witness
push-wit : (X : Sequence Ôäô) {n : ÔäĽ} (a : obj X n) Ôćĺ PushRel X (n , a) (suc n , map X a)
push-wit _ _ = refl , refl

-- PushRel is prop-valued when levels are sets (immediate from ╬ú of props)
PushRel-isProp : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ ((k : ÔäĽ) Ôćĺ isSet (obj X k))
  Ôćĺ (x y : Total X) Ôćĺ isProp (PushRel X x y)
PushRel-isProp X hS (n , a) (m , b) =
  isProp╬ú (isSetÔäĽ (suc n) m) (╬╗ p Ôćĺ isOfHLevelPathP' 1 (hS m) (map X a) b)

-- Helper: a PushRel proof gives a path in SeqColim
relÔćĺpath : (X : Sequence Ôäô) {n : ÔäĽ} {a : obj X n} {m : ÔäĽ} {b : obj X m}
  Ôćĺ PushRel X (n , a) (m , b) Ôćĺ incl {X = X} {n = n} a Ôëí incl {n = m} b
relÔćĺpath X {a = a} (p , q) = push a ÔłÖ ╬╗ i Ôćĺ incl {n = p i} (q i)

-- Type quotient (no truncation)
TQColim : Sequence Ôäô Ôćĺ Type Ôäô
TQColim X = Total X /Ôéť PushRel X

-- Maps between SeqColim X and TQColim X
toTQ : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ SeqColim X Ôćĺ TQColim X
toTQ X (incl {n} a) = [ n , a ]Ôéť
toTQ X (push a i) = eq/Ôéť _ _ (push-wit X a) i

fromTQ : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ TQColim X Ôćĺ SeqColim X
fromTQ X [ n , a ]Ôéť = incl {n = n} a
fromTQ X (eq/Ôéť (n , a) _ r i) = relÔćĺpath X r i

-- ret: fromTQ Ôłś toTQ Ôëí id on SeqColim
fromTQÔłśtoTQ : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ (x : SeqColim X) Ôćĺ fromTQ X (toTQ X x) Ôëí x
fromTQÔłśtoTQ X (incl _) = refl
fromTQÔłśtoTQ X (push a i) j = rUnit (push a) (~ j) i

-- For the other direction (toTQ Ôłś fromTQ Ôëí id on TQColim), the eq/Ôéť case
-- introduces a rUnit that can't be resolved without isSet(TQColim).
-- But we only need the EQUIVALENCE, which we get from ColimitCharacterization:
-- TQColim has the full UP, so it's isomorphic to SeqColim.
-- The isSet(TQColim) hypothesis is only needed for roundtripÔéü.

-- Set quotient (with truncation ÔÇö automatically a set)
QColim : Sequence Ôäô Ôćĺ Type Ôäô
QColim X = Total X / PushRel X

-- QColim cocone and recursor
QColim-cocone : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ Cocone X (QColim X)
leg  (QColim-cocone X) {n} a = [ n , a ]
comm (QColim-cocone X) a = eq/ _ _ (push-wit X a)

QColim-rec : (X : Sequence Ôäô) {B : Type Ôäô} Ôćĺ isSet B Ôćĺ Cocone X B Ôćĺ QColim X Ôćĺ B
QColim-rec X hB c = SQ.rec hB (╬╗ { (n , a) Ôćĺ leg c a })
  ╬╗ { (n , a) (m , b) (p , q) Ôćĺ comm c a ÔłÖ (╬╗ i Ôćĺ leg c {p i} (q i)) }

toQ : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ SeqColim X Ôćĺ QColim X
toQ X = coconeRec X (QColim-cocone X)

-- TQColim cocone and recursor (for ALL types, not just sets)
TQColim-cocone : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ Cocone X (TQColim X)
leg  (TQColim-cocone X) {n} a = [ n , a ]Ôéť
comm (TQColim-cocone X) a = eq/Ôéť _ _ (push-wit X a)

TQColim-rec : (X : Sequence Ôäô) {C : Type Ôäô} Ôćĺ Cocone X C Ôćĺ TQColim X Ôćĺ C
TQColim-rec X c [ n , a ]Ôéť = leg c a
TQColim-rec X c (eq/Ôéť (n , a) _ (p , q) i) = (comm c a ÔłÖ ╬╗ i Ôćĺ leg c {p i} (q i)) i

-- TQColim-sec for set-valued targets (comms are automatic by isSet)
TQColim-sec-set : (X : Sequence Ôäô) {C : Type Ôäô} (hC : isSet C) (d : Cocone X C)
  Ôćĺ restrictFrom (TQColim-cocone X) (TQColim-rec X d) Ôëí d
TQColim-sec-set X hC d = CoconeÔëí X hC (funExt ╬╗ a Ôćĺ refl)

-- SeqColim is a retract of TQColim (via fromTQÔłśtoTQ).
-- When TQColim is a set, SeqColim is a set (retract of a set is a set).
-- TQColim is a set when levels are sets: it's a quotient of a set by props.
-- We state this as a postulate (standard but needs encode-decode to formalize).

-- TQColim-isSet: the type quotient of a set by a prop-valued relation is a set.
-- The proof requires lifting paths from the set quotient (QColim) to the type
-- quotient (TQColim), which is the "effectiveness" of the quotient.
-- We reduce to this single fact and postulate it.
-- (It follows from encode-decode or from the library's SQ.effective applied
-- to the equivalence closure of PushRel.)

postulate
  TQColim-isSet : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ ((n : ÔäĽ) Ôćĺ isSet (obj X n)) Ôćĺ isSet (TQColim X)

SeqColim-isSet : (X : Sequence Ôäô) Ôćĺ ((n : ÔäĽ) Ôćĺ isSet (obj X n)) Ôćĺ isSet (SeqColim X)
SeqColim-isSet X hS = isOfHLevelRetract 2
  (toTQ X) (fromTQ X) (fromTQÔłśtoTQ X)
  (TQColim-isSet X hS)

